        <a name="origin"></a>
        <h3>What  is the origin of the name &quot;Unitarian Universalist&quot;?</h3>
        <p>Unitarian  Universalism emerged from two different religions: Unitarianism and  Universalism. 
        Both Unitarianism and Universalism started in Europe hundreds of  years ago. The Universalist 
        Church of America was founded by 1793, and the  American Unitarian Association by 1825. 
        In 1961, these denominations  consolidated to form the new religion of Unitarian Universalism. 
        For more  information, <a href="http://www.uua.org/publications/pamphlets/introductions/151249.shtml" target="_blank">click here</a>.</p>
