        <a name="member"></a>
        <h3>How  does one become a member of CVUUF?</h3>
The Path to Membership is a Journey to a Deeper Commitment. We hope that your relationship with Conejo Valley Unitarian Universalist Fellowship 
will be spiritually, intellectually, and emotionally rewarding.         <p>If  you are ready to join our congregation, it's easy to become a member. Our path  to membership includes four steps:</p>
        <ul class="greenBulletList">
        	<li>To attend our &quot;Path to Membership&quot; class which provides an introduction  to the congregation and to the principles and history of Unitarian  Universalism.</li>
            <li>To sign our membership book and thereby declare yourself a part of the  community.</li>
            <li>To pledge a financial contribution to the church. The amount is your personal  decision. There are no minimums.</li>
            <li> To attend to your spiritual practice, through Sunday services, affinity or small groups, service on committee, and outreach opportunities.</li>
            
        </ul>
We are pleased you have chosen to worship with us, and we invite you to participate in our programs and activities, 
whether or not you are ready for full membership. When you are ready, membership will be a natural step, a way to 
express your joy in &mdash; and responsibility for &mdash; this faith community.
